answers.body_markdown:
You&#39;re off by one (a very common source of errors). Of note is that `rand.nextInt(n)` will return a value from `0` to `n - 1`. You want

    int a = 1 + rand.nextInt(4);

Also, make sure you reuse that `SecureRandom` instance (don&#39;t recreate it in a loop for example).

